classreader
Interface ClassReader

All Known Implementing Classes:
ClassReaderImpl
public interface ClassReader

A ClassReader provides methods for reading from a stream that are relevant in the context of parsing a binary file, especially a class file in this context.

Author:
Werner Hahn

readBytesFully

void readBytesFully(byte[] buffer)
Reads bytes from the underlying stream until the provided buffer is full. This method behaves like readBytesFully(buffer, 0, buffer.length.

Parameters:
buffer - the buffer to fill

readBytesFully

void readBytesFully(byte[] buffer,
                    int offset,
                    int length)
Reads bytes from the underlying stream until the provided buffer is full. length bytes are written into the buffer starting from position offset.

Parameters:
buffer - the buffer to fill
offset - the position in the buffer to begin with
length - the number of bytes to read
